<TEXT>
the government will file new charges 
accusing sen juan ponce enrile of participating in decembers 
failed coup an official said wednesday 
the move comes a day after the supreme court rejected a previous 
indictment against enrile and 22 others saying the charges were 
legally invalid 
enrile and the others were charged with rebellion combined with 
murder in connection with the dec 19 coup attempt that left 113 
people dead and more than 600 wounded 
on tuesday chief justice marcelo fernan said the supreme court 
voted 112 against reviewing a 1956 court decision thereby 
overturning the combined charges two justices were absent or 
abstained fernan said 
presidential press secretary tomas gomez said the government had 
enough evidence to charge enrile with the lesser charge of 
rebellion murder is punishable by life imprisonment but rebellion 
carries a prison sentence of six to 12 years 
the quality of the evidence has not been diminished 
whatsoever gomez said in a radio interview wednesday the 
government will now file a case based on rebellion 
in 1956 the court ruled that killings occurring during an armed 
uprising should be treated differently than crimes with common 
motives the court said defendants should be charged with rebellion 
and not murder 
defendants in rebellion cases are allowed bail bail is generally 
denied in murder cases 
mrs aquinos legal adviser adolfo azcuna said the government 
may seek reconsideration in the philippines supreme court rulings 
become final after 10 days during which parties to the case can ask 
for reconsideration 
in editorials wednesday several newspapers accused mrs aquino 
of poor judgment in charging enrile with the combined offense 
the daily globe published by mrs aquinos former speechwriter 
teodoro locsin said the government had lost and lost miserably 
sen john osmena said the ruling meant the governments attempt 
to bend the law to intimidate those who do not agree with the 
administration has been foiled 
after the vote enrile said i think the supreme court 
although the members are all appointees of president aquino remains 
faithful to their role as guardians of liberty i am happy for the 
country 
enrile a former defense minister was arrested in february the 
supreme court released him on bail two weeks later pending a 
decision on the validity of the charge 
enrile has denied any role in the uprising enrile played a key 
role in the 1986 military mutiny that triggered the people power 
revolution that propelled mrs aquino to power 
enrile was fired in november 1986 after a failed coup by his 
followers 
</TEXT>
