<TEXT>
former san francisco mayor dianne feinstein 
took an early lead over attorney general john van de kamp on tuesday 
in a hotly contested race for the democratic nomination for 
governor voters also considered a proposal to double state gasoline 
taxes 
with 1 percent of the precincts reporting feinstein had 49557 
votes or 52 percent to van de kamps 40271 votes or 42 percent 
the feinsteinvan de kamp race headlined a lengthy state ballot 
with us sen pete wilson facing only token opposition for the gop 
nomination for governor 
one ballot measure called for raising the gas tax from 9 to 18 
cents per gallon to renew a financially starved highway building 
program it was ahead in the early returns with 100425 yes votes 
or 53 percent to 88327 no votes or 47 percent 
other state races featured new political faces with familiar 
family names 
in the republican race for state treasurer incumbent tom hayes 
led angela bay buchanan former us treasurer and sister of 
conservative commentator pat buchanan by a 65to35 percent margin 
kathleen brown daughter of former gov pat brown and sister of 
former gov jerry brown was leading the democratic treasurers race 
against wesley sanders jr by 59 percent to 41 percent 
two other statewide races had a unique family tie 
democratic secretary of state march fong eu was seeking a fifth 
term as the states chief election officer and highest ranking 
chineseamerican official while her son matt fong was unopposed 
for the republican nomination for state controller 
californias 45 congressional races included several interesting 
contests 
democratic incumbent jim bates faced a strong challenge in a san 
diego primary because of his formal rebuke by the house ethics 
committee for sexual harassment of women employees 
actor ralph waite papa walton of the television series was 
seeking the democratic nomination for a seat now held by republican 
al mccandless in the palm springs area 
tim stoen former attorney for peoples temple before the cults 
mass suicide with 912 deaths over a decade ago was seeking the 
republican nomination to oppose democratic incumbent doug bosco in 
californias north coast redwood country 
in other local races attorney william graysen who represented 
actress zsa zsa gabor in her copslapping trial was running for a 
state senate seat from beverly hills and oakland mayor lionel 
wilson was the underdog in his reelection bid because of the 
controversy over his part in oaklands failed bid to bring the los 
angeles raiders back to oakland 
the proposed gas tax hike which would mark a symbolic end to the 
tax revolt that began with passage of proposition 13 in 1978 was 
among several measures on the statewide ballot 
companion bond measures would start a multibilliondollar program 
of new commuter train service 
another ballot proposition would take control of reapportionment 
of congressional and legislative districts out the hands of the 
democratic leadership of the legislature 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
feinsteins bid for the democratic nomination for governor marked 
the first serious attempt by a woman to win californias chief job 
a fact that overshadowed most other issues in her race against van 
de kamp a less telegenic but politically wellconnected prosecutor 
abortion was a major issue for all of the major candidates to 
succeed retiring republican george deukmejian as governor even 
though all three were prochoice 
feinstein and van de kamp competed over who was the most 
effective champion of a womans right to choose the limited 
opposition raised in the gop primary against wilson a moderate 
republican who never touted his prochoice stand came from 
antiabortion activists 
norma mccorvey the jane roe in roe vs wade the us 
supreme court case that established a womans right to an abortion 
made a lastminute campaign appearance for van de kamp 
feinstein campaigned as tough on crime trying to seize an issue 
that seemed more likely to belong to her opponent 
she ran a latecampaign tv ad criticizing van de kamp for 
declining to prosecute a suspect in the hillside strangler case in 
which 10 people were killed van de kamp was the los angeles 
district attorney at the time and the suspect angelo buono was 
later convicted of murder after the state attorney general stepped 
into the case 
van de kamp called the criticism baloney 
the gasoline tax measure proposition 111 marked a political 
turning point for the state 
opponents noted that the measure which would raise 155 billion 
over the next decade would be the largest tax hike in the states 
history supporters warned that defeat of the proposal would bring 
californias highway construction program to a halt during an era of 
the fastest population growth in decades 
