south korean president roh taewoo said 
monday that he and soviet president mikhail s gorbachev have agreed 
to end 45 years of cold war animosity by establishing diplomatic 
relations between their countries 
as a result of my meeting with president gorbachev today 
normal bilateral relations between our countries will be restored 
roh said 
the south korean leader said discussions would continue toward 
that end but that no dates had been set 
the gorbachevroh meeting which took place at the end of 
gorbachevs visit to the united states was the first between 
leaders of the two nations since korea was partitioned more than 
four decades ago 
the cold war ice on the korean peninsula now has begun to 
crack roh told reporters 
though nothing was put in writing he said the two countries plan 
to boost economic and trade ties 
the soviet president was more vague in his summation of the 
meeting 
we will let the fruit grow ripe and when the fruit grows ripe 
we will eat it gorbachev told reporters outside the soviet consul 
generals home before departing san francisco for home at the end 
of a fiveday us visit 
korean officials have called friendlier ties with the soviet 
union a cornerstone of the roh administration 
the two countries have had an unstable relationship since the 
formation of south korea at the end of world war ii but the 
hostility began to abate in 1988 when the soviets announced they 
would participate in the seoul olympics 
roh plans to meet with president bush in washington on wednesday 
to brief him on his talk with gorbachev and to discuss the 
ussoviet summit which ended sunday 
north korea became a communist satellite state in 1948 in 1950 
soviet leader josef stalin promised to support north koreas 
invasion of the south an attack that led to three years of war that 
ended with an armistice but no peace treaty 
it is estimated that the soviet union now supplies 70 percent of 
north koreas military supplies including advanced weapons systems 
an improved relationship between the soviet union and south korea 
could benefit the united states by making possible an accelerated 
withdrawal of us troops from south korea the united states 
already has announced plans to withdraw 7000 of its 43000 troops 
during the next two years 
roh met sunday with top us state department officials 
including richard solomon the assistant secretary of state for east 
asian and pacific affairs who briefed him on the gorbachevbush 
summit 
