<TEXT>
the presbyterian church faced with 
potentially bitter battles over abortion and the ordination of 
homosexuals decided monday to wait until next year to tackle the 
issues 
commissioners to the 202nd general assembly of the presbyterian 
church usa voted overwhelmingly monday to postpone until 1991 
action on resolutions dealing with a variety of such issues they 
ranged from a call for the church to withdraw from an abortion 
rights group to a proposal to allow local church bodies to ordain 
homosexuals 
i feel that debate on this matter results in high feelings 
emotion divisiveness said the rev rush otey of the greater 
atlanta presbytery theres a time for the church to speak 
theres a time for the church to be silent 
but representatives of an antiabortion group charged the 
denomination lacked the moral courage to address the issues 
there is a desire to see the issue in a political sense but a 
reluctance to deal with it as a moral issue said terry 
schlossberg executive director of presbyterians prolife 
the assembly voted late monday to take away semiofficial status 
from 21 private church organizations including some of its severest 
liberal and conservative critics 
despite criticism that they were tring to reduce voices of 
dissent within the church nearly 80 percent of the commisioners 
voted to delete a portion of the churchs book of order that gives 
groups such as presbyterians for lesbiangay concerns and 
presbyterians prolife the right to be officially represented at the 
general assembly and church meetings 
the proposal goes to the churchs 177 presbyteries a majority of 
the regional bodies must approve the change for it to take effect 
a task force on sexuality is expected to report on both 
homosexuality and abortion to the 1991 general assembly the church 
supports legalized abortion and opposes the ordination of 
homosexuals 
in other business monday the assembly voted to create a church 
office for the environment and to call for stricter gun control laws 
two of the resolutions which were deferred called for church 
agencies to withdraw from the religious coalition on abortion rights 
and to oppose lateterm abortions where the fetus could survive 
outside the womb 
the church embroiled in a dispute over the distribution of 
sexually explicit literature to a youth meeting by a 
churchrecognized gay caucus also postponed until 1991 a decision 
on whether to allow local church bodies to ordain homsexuals 
the issue of homosexuality heated up in the 29 millionmember 
denomination last summer when presbyterians lesbiangay concerns 
distributed brochures detailing the sexual practices of homosexuals 
to high school and college students attending a church meeting at 
purdue university the brochures discussed both oral and anal sex 
and gave explicit instructions in the use of condoms 
