<TEXT>
the 1990 census has counted 87 percent of 
american households an official said tuesday 
spokesman ray bancroft said the households had been counted in 
the mail and doortodoor portions of the census which is 
continuing 
bancroft said the 90 percent level could be reached within a 
week but that the last 10 percent is the hardest to count 
people who mailed back their census forms in march were the 
easiest to tally and census workers have added to that total by 
visiting the homes of those who didnt get forms in the mail or 
failed to send them back 
now they are trying to count people who are reluctant to 
cooperate with government officials are away from home or are so 
busy working that they are hard to find 
the census mandated every 10 years by the constitution is used 
to redistribute seats in the house of representatives and to divide 
billions of dollars in federal aid among state and communities 
nearly 100 million forms were mailed in april 
bancroft said census maps of local communities were being sent to 
about 39000 local governments 
by the end of august each community will receive a count of the 
number of housing units on each block and the total population of 
the community local officials will have 15 days to report any 
discrepancies between their counts and the census report 
meanwhile processing is running well ahead of the rate set 10 
years ago bancroft said 
the 1980 census forms were kept at local offices until the area 
count was complete then shipped en masse to processing centers 
that meant computer processing didnt begin until august 1980 
this year forms are shipped to the seven processing centers as 
they are collected microfilming and computer processing has already 
begun 
