coming or going conciliatory or sharptongued in the 
sundrenched bay area on monday or the cold drizzle of the upper 
midwest on sunday soviet president mikhail gorbachev never failed 
to draw a crowd 
he could be unpredictable he accommodated knots of screaming 
protesters and smiling families with equal aplomb lingering longest 
among those crowds whose adulation swelled until the secret service 
agents guarding him were red with frustration and the elected 
officials squiring him were green with envy 
in san francisco his wife raisa bolted from the motorcade at 
one point and swooped down unannounced on fishermans wharf 
stepping out of the car just long enough to ring the bell on a cable 
car 
the gorbachevs gave the impression that they went where they 
wanted saw what they wanted and said what they wanted to say 
though many of the impromptu jaunts no doubt were conceived as 
photo opportunities rather than gettingtoknowyou excursions 
their skill and savvy at every turn earned them respect even if it 
sometimes came grudgingly 
at about 3 pm sunday gorbachev nixed a scheduled visit to a 
family farm outside minneapolis inside the hubert humphrey 
metrodome which had been converted into a media center for the 
visit a harried secret service agent put down his radio and threw 
up his hands 
the guy is a nightmare jumps out of the car when he wants to 
and strolls any place he feels like youve seen the things in the 
newspapers about us not knowing whats going on well he said 
theyre true 
if that was the case a reporter asked who was calling the shots 
the agent looked toward the oversized tv screen high above the 
wall in left centerfield on it the gorbachev motorcade was 
pictured zooming back toward downtown 
id bet its him the agent said the guy in the car 
