police shot to death 13 suspected sikh 
extremists and at least 22 other people were killed in a renewed 
bout of separatist violence in the northern state of punjab news 
reports said tuesday 
the killings occurred in separate incidents during a 24hour 
period ending tuesday night they were reported on the sixth 
anniversary of an indian army raid on the sikhs holiest shrine the 
golden temple 
at least 1200 people were killed when troops backed by heavy 
artillery attacked the temple in amritsar on june 3 1984 to flush 
out sikh militants entrenched inside the assault lasted four days 
the government increased security around the golden temple on 
tuesday and prohibited a special congregation planned for inside the 
shrine to mark the anniversary of the raid the press trust of india 
news agency reported 
in a dispatch from the punjab state capital of chandigarh pti 
said the 13 sikhs killed by police included three who were about to 
set fire to a railroad station building in punjab early tuesday 
police found two ak47 assault rifles kerosene cans and 
matchboxes with the victims pti said 
it said the three men belonged to the khalistan commando force 
one of the several militant groups in punjab fighting for a separate 
sikh homeland khalistan is the name of the sikhs proposed homeland 
pti said among the other militants killed were harcharan singh of 
the khalistan liberation front and kashmira singh a selfstyled 
lieutenant general of babbar khalsa or the pure lion 
the two groups and the khalistan commando force are among the top 
sikh militant organizations in punjab a rich farming state 
bordering pakistan 
in other violence blamed on the sikh campaign press trust said 
five armed youths raided a house in chogwan village 230 miles north 
of new delhi and fatally shot a couple and their daughter late 
monday 
in another incident a man and his daughter were burned to death 
by unidentified assailants pti said it did not say where or when 
it happened 
it said extremists killed 17 other people in separate incidents 
in the state but did not give details 
the deaths raised to 1036 the number of people killed this year 
in the sikh separatist violence many of the victims have been from 
the states minority hindu community but militants have also 
targeted sikhs who do not support their cause 
sikh militants have been fighting since 1982 for an independent 
homeland in punjab where sikhs are in a slight majority over 
hindus the sikhs claim they are discriminated against by the 
hindus who make up 82 percent of indias 880 million people 
