with gorbachev tried to put the best face on yeltsins election 
saying it could help the soviet leader accelerate the pace of 
reforms 
gorbachevs latest reform package was foundering during his 
absence as shoppers continued the rush on stores they began after 
prime minister nikolai i ryzhkov announced an economic reform 
package that would triple the price of bread on july 1 and double 
the cost of most other food starting jan 1 
yeltsin in a kremlin news conference wednesday called for 
ryzhkovs resignation criticized the price hikes and demanded 
faster transition to a market economy 
gorbachev may have a chance to regain the initiative in domestic 
affairs in an address he is scheduled to deliver on his trip to the 
two houses of the soviet legislature sometime this week the day for 
the speech has not been announced 
