the khmer rouge was ready to accept a ceasefire or statements 
about the desirability of a supreme national council but not a 
linkage between them particularly a time linkage a foreign 
ministry official said on condition of anonymity 
a second foreign ministry official said khmer rouge nominal 
leader khieu samphan had a rather limited mandate for the talks 
anything beyond that mandate he had great trouble accepting 
the conference was heralded as a steppingstone to a cambodia 
peace conference set for paris in july 
the final documents arrived late for the signing ceremony tuesday 
evening drawing an apology from masaharu kohno a southeast asia 
division chief in the foreign ministry 
sihanouk signed the communique with hun sen premier of the phnom 
penh government and japanese foreign minister taro nakayama acted 
as chairman the two cambodians embraced then drank a champagne 
toast to peace in cambodia 
at a news conference sihanouk said fighting would continue in 
cambodia but not involving the guerrilla force headed by his son 
prince ranariddh or that of his conservative partner former 
premier son sann 
from now on the ranariddhists and the son sannists will stop 
fighting he said i can predict that there will be continuation 
of war in my country between the khmer rouge on one side and the 
viets and hun sennians on the other 
but a thai official speaking on condition of anonymity said it 
was one thing for sihanouk to say his forces should stop and another 
thing for the commanders in the field to heed the call 
western observers in bangkok have long noted a division between 
cambodian political figures like sihanouk who spend little time in 
the field and live comfortably elsewhere and their followers who 
have a steady flow of munitions to use as they see fit 
fighting was reported to be increasing in cambodia before the 
tokyo conference started 
if sihanouks prediction is borne out the chinesebacked khmer 
rouge would be isolated on the battlefield as well as in 
international opinion many have rejected the idea of the khmer 
rouge participating in any future government 
during the khmer rouges 197579 rule hundreds of thousands of 
people were killed or died of starvation the group was ousted by 
the vietnamese 
the khmer rouge is militarily the strongest guerrilla faction 
fighting the phnom penh government installed by hanoi 
the 67yearold sihanouk has headed the resistance since 1982 he 
says the khmer rouge killed five of his children but still believes 
the groups force is the strongest barrier to vietnamese 
encroachment on cambodia 
the sihanoukhun sen communique calls for all factions to use 
voluntary selfrestraint on force to refrain from offensive 
actions and to impose a military standstill 
the khmer rouge said in a statement it was ready to attend the 
paris conference 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

