<TEXT>
while south koreas political and trade relations 
with moscow develop japans ties to the soviet union are tied up in 
a longstanding dispute over tokyos demand for the return of islands 
seized by the soviets in world war ii 
the dispute has prevented the nations from signing a peace treaty 
since the war ended in 1945 and it was brought up during the 
superpower summit in washington 
president bush told prime minister toshiki kaifu of japan that he 
raised the issue with mikhail s gorbachev during their talks 
government spokesman misoji sakamoto said 
