francisco with president roh taewoo of south korea south korean 
officials predicted the unprecedented meeting would lead to 
diplomatic ties between seoul and moscow which were on opposite 
sides in the cold war 
the soviets are allies with communist north korea south koreas 
archenemy and they supported the north during the korean war 
but economic and political relations have warmed in recent years 
particularly since 1988 when the soviets participated in the seoul 
olympics despite a boycott by north korea 
