a mass grave believed to have been used by 
the rightist military has yielded 15 bound and bulletriddled bodies 
and could conceal as many more officials said tuesday 
the corpses in the atacama desert are believed to be those of 
leftists rounded up and killed by army troops after a 1973 coup 
human rights officials said the discovery prompted renewed calls by 
relatives groups for the new civilian government to prosecute 
officers 
digging continued tuesday under judicial supervision at the 
longsecret grave outside the fishing village of pisagua on the 
pacific coast 1185 miles north of santiago 
rights activists and government officials said the body count had 
risen from eight on sunday to 15 late monday digging began saturday 
belisario velasco an interior ministry subsecretary told 
