gulfstream aerospace corp the nations 
largest producer of corporate and business jets is developing a 
device to reduce jet engine noise on commercial airlines the 
companys chairman said tuesday 
allen e paulson said he has filed for a patent on the device 
which he said will extend the life of planes cut the operating 
costs and help meet government regulations 
he said it could be in production within two years 
paulson made the announcement at the opening session of the 
companys annual owners and operators workshop 
he did not provide details on how the device will work but said 
he finalized its design earlier this year 
i worked on it to be applied first to gulfstream iis and iiis 
but it can be adapted to most all of the existing airliners in 
operation he said 
the device would fill a need created by a growing federal push 
for noise abatement around major airports he said and could open 
up a whole new ballgame for savannahbased gulfstream 
</TEXT>
