sematech officials pledged to continue 
efforts to make the united states preeminent in hightechnology 
despite the loss of sematech leader robert noyce but industry 
analysts and politicians said the research group cannot get 
complacent about its federal funding 
noyce 62 known internationally as a founding father of the 
silicon valley and coinventor of the integrated circuit died 
sunday morning of cardiac arrest 
he was chairman of sematech the austinbased research group of 
14 technology companies which includes international business 
machines corp american telephone amp telegraph co texas 
instruments inc and motorola inc 
he commanded respect in the hightech industry and had the 
political skills to win points in washington he became the major 
national spokesman for government intervention in the semiconductor 
war with japan 
directors of the consortium are stepping up their effort to 
replace noyce 
the board understands that it must resolve this issue 
expeditiously said charles sporck sematechs board chairman and 
head of the search committee 
in the interim sematech will be run by two men who noyce 
frequently left in charge of daytoday operations chief operating 
office turner hasty 59 a veteran researcher and business executive 
who came to sematech from texas instruments and chief 
administrative officer peter mills 39 a former computer executive 
and a former greater austin chamber of commerce executive 
sematech leaders and us rep jj pickle dtexas spoke to 
sematech employees monday 
pickle a key backer of the research project assured workers 
that sematechs requested 100 million in federal funds for 1991 
remained strong sematech receives half its 200 million annual 
budget from the government and the remaining funds from its member 
companies 
the unprecedented privatepublic venture has provoked some 
criticism in congress but the bush administration has proposed 
continued funding for sematech for the 1991 fiscal year which 
starts in october 
but pickle cautioned that sematech cannot let its guard down and 
must move quickly to fill the top job 
they need to get the best person as quickly as they can so 
they can move forward with the program the austin 
americanstatesman reported tuesday 
finding someone of noyces caliber wont be easy said dan 
hutcheson president of vlsi research in san jose calif a man 
like noyce comes along maybe once every two centuries hutcheson 
said 
they are going to have to have to look long and hard to find 
someone of his stature and background to take it over he said 
