whirlpool corp and a leading japanese 
producer of consumer and electronic goods announced tuesday they 
have signed a joint venture to produce vacuum cleaners for the north 
american market 
the joint venture of whirlpool which is based in benton harbor 
mich and matsushita electric industrial co ltd of osaka japan 
will own and operate whirlpools vacuum manufacturing plant in 
danville 
according to the announcement whirlpool will assist the joint 
venture in maintaining and expanding its floor care product business 
relationship with sears roebuck and co the plant in danville 
produces a full line of canister upright and central vacuum 
cleaners for sears under the kenmore brand name 
whirlpool will have continued management involvement to assure 
continuity in marketing and manufacturing and the company also will 
have representation on the board of directors whirlpool will report 
an aftertax gain on the sale of an interest in the joint venture at 
the time of closing 
matsushita currently imports panasonic brand vacuum cleaners to 
the united states and is expected to use the kentucky facility to 
expand its manufacturing and marketing base in north america 
matsushita is the worlds leading manufacturer of consumer and 
industrial electronics products with annual sales of nearly 38 
billion it has production facilities and sales offices in 38 
countries and 198000 employees worldwide the company markets 
14000 different electronics products under the panasonic technics 
quasar and national brand names 
whirlpool is the worlds leading manufacturer and marketer of 
major home appliances the company manufactures in 10 countries and 
markets products under nine major brand names in more than 45 
countries 
on feb 9 whirlpool announced that it was planning to sell its 
danville plant and the floorcare operation there 
whirlpool said it decided to sell the floorcare operation 
because it didnt have the resources other companies had for 
continued growth and profitability in the long term the company 
said it had decided to concentrate on the manufacture of trash 
compactors and ice makers 
whirlpool already has begun the phaseout of its two other major 
operations trash compactors and ice makers at the danville 
plant the operations are being moved to other whirlpool plants 
some 250 of whirlpools 1000 danville employees are involved in 
the manufacture of trash compactors and another 50 are involving in 
making ice makers the rest are assigned to the floor care division 
