<TEXT>
bankers are paying more attention to the 
impact of environmental concerns on their industry and on business 
in general participants in a worldwide banking convention said 
tuesday 
when banks are asked to finance a factory or other industrial 
operation they increasingly explore the potential environmental 
impact of the project before giving approval said r donald 
fullerton chairman and chief executive of canadian imperial bank of 
commerce 
were in an early learning process he told reporters at the 
international monetary conference we are paying more attention to 
the kinds of projects we are financing for potential environmental 
impact he said fullerton called such concern a reasonably new 
development 
another concern for banks is the environmental impact of their 
own operations said fullerton who was chairman of a panel on the 
environment at the annual banking convention 
we have a massive papergenerating machine that we need to deal 
with he said without offering a solution 
fullerton said the bankers at the closeddoor meetings agreed 
that the environment was a major issue that the banking community 
will have to pay attention to 
for industry in general the environmental aspects have become 
a new bottom line said one of the panelists alex krauer 
chairman and managing director of cibageigy ltd of basel 
switzerland 
we are part of the problem but also want to be part of the 
solution krauer told reporters 
at their private session the bankers heard an address by frank 
press president of the national academy of sciences who said he 
believes business executives are genuinely concerned about the 
impact of their operations on the environment according to a text 
of his speech 
i dont think i am being unfair if i observe that 20 years ago 
many companies treated environmental concerns as something to 
ignore deflect or fight he said today their perceptions and 
actions have changed greatly 
