bahamas 
the plan calls for miamibased eastern to purchase 59 percent of 
bar harbor airways from sister carrier continental airlines and 
expand its commuter service 
eastern which already owns 41 percent of bar harbor operates 
the florida service as its eastern express subsidiary said 
spokeswoman karen ceremsak 
no price was announced for easterns acquisition of continentals 
share said ms ceremsak 
under the pact continental would take over bar harbors 
operations in the northeast the carrier presently has 148 daily 
flights under the continental express logo from hubs in newark 
nj new yorks la guardia airport and boston 
because eastern will only receive bar harbors smaller southern 
operations continental will pay the carrier 3 million and also 
forgive all debt owed by bar harbor said peggy mahoney a 
spokeswoman at houstonbased continental express 
the deal if approved would settle all claims by eastern against 
bar harbor or continental in connection with bar harbor operations 
said ms ceremsak 
bar harbor facing growing competition from american airlines and 
pan am world airways commuter services had planned to halt its 
southern flights on sunday 
this plan averts the closing and we have plans to expand 
said ms ceremsak 
eastern plans to maintain bar harbors present 47 daily flights 
from miami to 11 cities in florida and the bahamas also eastern 
said it plans to increase miami service and add flights from key 
west to fort myers and naples 
all 300 bar harbor employees in florida and the bahamas will keep 
their jobs under eastern express the carrier said 
eastern said it may increase its commuter operation to more than 
70 daily departures to 16 cities by late summer 
the plan must receive approval from the us department of 
transportation and us bankruptcy court in new york eastern filed 
for chapter 11 bankruptcy protection shortly after a strike by 
machinists pilots and flight attendants in march 1989 
martin shugrue the courtappointed trustee overseeing eastern 
said the bar harbor deal is part of a strategy to preserve our 
longterm florida presence 
but eastern will also face competition from other carriers 
seeking to feed their miami hubs with commuter flights 
american operates 33 flights from miami under american eagle and 
plans aggressive expansion in coming years pan am express began 
service with 25 flights from miami last month and hopes to add up to 
five more destinations this fall 
</TEXT>
